A homeless man was struck and killed by a hit-and-run driver while crossing the street in East New York, Brooklyn, police said. Witnesses told authorities that an unidentified man in his 60s was pushing a shopping cart along 108th Street, near Stanley Avenue shortly after 4 a.m. Saturday when he was mowed down by an unknown driver traveling northbound on 108th Street, cops said. The hit-and-run driver sped off and the victim was pronounced dead at the scene, police said. There are no arrests.